<package name="spotify-easyrpm" project="openSUSE:Factory">
  <title>Spotify-EasyRPM</title>
  <description>Spotify-EasyRPM is a bash script designed to download the latest debian package from the Spotify repository and convert it into an RPM

 Features
 
 * Set up a build enviornment on your PC and install rpm-build 
 * Auto download the latest version of Spotify
 * Convert the debian package to RPM format
 * Install the Spotify RPM
 * Set up a automated cron job
 * Create a local filesystem repo so Spotify can be updated alongside regular updates
 * Fully unattended mode</description>
  <devel project="multimedia:apps" package="spotify-easyrpm"/>
</package>
